Feel like I'm usually unwilling to take this event, too much risk of losing a relic I care about

The flavor here is really cool, ranwid is shuffling items around between heroes and villains, mirroring the original event and expanding their character. Sadly, it's a pretty weak event most of the time, because it chooses the relic at random for you, which will often mean that it picks ones you really want to keep, or are just generally good. You can't specifically throw away useless, used up, or very weak relics like ceramic fish, omamori, or stone calendar. On top of that, the rewards here are very lackluster, the potions are directly trading out long term strength for short term strength, the souls aren't going to help until you can find a shop (and aren't that significant an amount). 

I haven't ever been offered the rare card for a relic I was okay with losing, so I actually don't know the specifics of how it works. Is it like a boss rare reward (pick 1 of 3), or are you just handed 1 rare completely at random?
